message.en_US: You look at it, you buy it.

message.ja_JP:
一度手に取ったら
買ってくださいね。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/01/10]

message.en_US: Well look who it is!

message.de_DE: Ach, wen haben wir denn da?
message.ja_JP: レアじゃないか！<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/01/10]

message.en_US: Hi!
message.pt_BR: Oi!
message.de_DE: Hi!

message.en_US: I must admit, I was expecting you.
message.pt_BR: Devo admitir que estava esperando por você.
message.de_DE: Ich muss gestehen, dass ich dich erwartet habe.
message.zh_CN: 老实说，我确实在等你来着。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/01/10]

正直に言えば、
君が来るんじゃないかと
期待してたよ。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/01/10]

message.en_US: Yet you still managed to surprise me.

message.de_DE: Und doch hast du es geschafft, mich zu überraschen.

message.ja_JP:
だが、それでも君は
私を驚かせてくれたね。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/01/10]
message.zh_TW: 不過你還是嚇了我一跳。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/01/10]

message.en_US: Haha, now don't get cocky on an old man.

message.de_DE: Hoahoahoa, werde bloß nicht übermütig.

message.ja_JP:
はは、この老いぼれを
あまりいじめないでくれよ。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/01/10]

message.en_US: Anyway... there's only one more piece missing in our little puzzle.
message.pt_BR: Mudando de assunto... falta apenas mais uma peça em nosso pequeno quebra-cabeça.
message.de_DE: Also... Es fehlt nur noch ein Teil in unserem kleinen Puzzle.
message.zh_CN: 总之...现在谜题还剩下最后一片碎片。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/02/01]
message.ja_JP:
それはさておき...私たちの
ちょっとした謎解きは、
あとピースひとつで完成する。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/02/01]
message.ko_KR: 아무튼... 이제 퍼즐의 한 조각만 있으면 된단다.<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/02/01]

message.en_US: Should we find it, I might be able to fulfill my promise to my kids...
message.pt_BR: Se a encontrarmos, talvez eu consiga cumprir minha promessa aos meus filhos.
message.de_DE: Sollten wir es finden, könnte ich mein Versprechen meinen Kindern gegenüber halten...
message.zh_CN: 要是能找到的话，也许我就能完成对孩子们的承诺...<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/01/10]
message.ja_JP:
もし見つけられれば、私は子供たちとの
約束を果たせるかもしれない...<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/01/10]
message.ko_KR: 그걸 찾으면 아이들에게 한 약속을 지킬 수 있어...<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/01/10]
message.zh_TW: 要是能找到的話，也許我就能完成對孩子們的承諾...<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/01/10]

message.en_US: No reason to look sad, little one.
message.pt_BR: Não há razão para ficar triste, baxinha.
message.de_DE: Kein Grund, so traurig zu gucken, Kleine.
message.ja_JP:
悲しい顔をする理由は
ないな、お嬢さん。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/01/10]
message.ko_KR: 슬픈 표정 지을 필요 없단다, 꼬마야.<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/01/10]

message.en_US: I'm sure if I can get them all in one place and talk to them this will all end well.

message.de_DE: Ich bin sicher, dass alles gut werden wird, wenn ich sie alle versammeln und mit ihnen reden kann.
message.zh_CN: 只要能把他们聚到一起，我跟他们聊聊一定能解决的。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/05/14]
message.ja_JP:
アイテムを一か所に集めて、
子供たちと話すことができれば、
すべてうまくいくだろう。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/05/14]
message.ko_KR: 조각을 전부 모은다면 아이들에게도 말해 좋은 결말을 맞이할 거란다.<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/05/14]
message.zh_TW: 只要能把他們聚到一起，我跟他們聊聊一定能解決的。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/05/14]

message.de_DE: [nickt]
message.ja_JP: [うなずく]<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/01/10]

message.en_US: Alright, the last ones are the \c[3]\v[item.515.name]\c[0].

よし、最後のひとつは

戻ってきたな。

message.pt_BR: [acena a cabeça]

message.ja_JP: [うなずく]<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/01/10]

message.en_US: Would you be willing to join us? It's only fair and I trust you.

message.en_US: [nods]
message.pt_BR: [acena a cabeça]
message.de_DE: [nickt]
message.ja_JP: [うなずく]<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/01/10]

message.en_US: Thanks, kiddo.

では、私は行くよ！
観測場で会おう。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/01/10]

message.en_US: Bye!

僕だけかな、彼が...\.\.

text.en_US: In \c[3]\v[area.forest.name]\c[0], locals indulge passionately in the art of poems. The most famous is called \c[3]A War in the Bellow\c[0] and goes like this:
text.pt_BR: Na \c[3]\v[area.forest.name]\c[0], os habitantes locais se entregam apaixonadamente à arte dos poemas. O mais famoso deles é chamado de \c[3]Uma Guerra no [???]\c[0] e começa assim:
text.de_DE: Die Bewohner des \c[3]Saphirgrats\c[0] frönen leidenschaftlich der Dichtkunst. Das berühmteste Gedicht trägt den Titel \c[3]Ein Krieg in der Brüllerei\c[0] und geht wie folgt:
text.zh_CN: \c[3]\v[area.forest.name]\c[0]的居民喜欢创作诗句。其中最有名的是\c[3]咆哮之战\c[0]，诗句如下：<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/01/10]
text.ja_JP:
\c[3]\v[area.forest.name]\c[0]において、地元民は熱心に
詩という芸術を楽しんだ。もっとも有名な

message.en_US: Hello.
message.pt_BR: Olá.
message.ja_JP: いらっしゃい。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.de_DE: Hallo.

message.en_US: Are you looking for a book?
message.pt_BR: Você está procurando um livro?
message.ja_JP: 本をお探しで？<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.de_DE: Suchst du nach einem Buch?

message.en_US: [shakes head]
message.pt_BR: [balança a cabeça]
message.ja_JP: [首を振る]<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.de_DE: [schüttelt Kopf]

message.en_US: Okay.
message.pt_BR: Ok.
message.ja_JP: そうですか。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.de_DE: Okay.

message.en_US: So...\. just so you know...
message.pt_BR: Então...\. só pra você saber...
message.ja_JP: その...\.一応お知らせしておくと...<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.de_DE: Also...\. Nur damit du's weißt...

message.en_US: This is a book store.
message.pt_BR: Aqui é uma livraria.
message.ja_JP: ここは本屋ですよ。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.de_DE: Das hier ist ein Buchladen.

message.en_US: Not sure what else you hope to find here.
message.pt_BR: Não faço ideia do que você pretende encontrar aqui.
message.ko_KR: 네가 어떤 책을 찾고 싶어 하는지 확실히 모르겠네.<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.ja_JP:
本以外のものは
見つからないと思いますが。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.de_DE: Keine Ahnung, was du hier sonst zu finden hoffst.

message.en_US: *sigh*
message.de_DE: *seufz*

message.en_US: What am I doing here?
message.pt_BR: O que eu estou fazendo aqui?
message.ja_JP: 私は何をしているのでしょうね？<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.de_DE: Was mach' ich hier eigentlich?

message.en_US: I came to this bustling city hoping to get a position in one of their libraries.
message.pt_BR: Eu vim pra essa cidade agitada na esperança de conseguir um trabalho em uma dessas bibliotecas.
message.zh_CN: 我来这座繁华的城市，是想进这里的图书馆。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.ko_KR: 난 저 도서관 중 한 곳에서 일을 구하려고 이 떠들썩한 도시에 왔어.<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.ja_JP:
私は大きな書庫の主になりたいという
夢を持って、この騒がしい街に
やってきたのです。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.de_DE: Ich kam in diese Stadt, weil ich gehofft hatte, hier eine Stelle in einer Bibliothek zu finden.
message.zh_TW: 我來這座繁華的城市，是想進這裡的圖書館。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]

message.en_US: Yet somehow I ended up in this tiny book store.
message.pt_BR: Porém, de alguma forma eu acabei nessa pequena livraria.
message.zh_CN: 没想到却落到了这个小书店里。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.ja_JP:
ですが結局、構えられたのは
この小さい本屋だけ。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.de_DE: Aber irgendwie bin ich in diesem mickrigen Buchladen gelandet.
message.zh_TW: 沒想到卻落到了這個小書店裡。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]

message.en_US: Why?
message.pt_BR: Por que?
message.ja_JP: どうして？<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.de_DE: Warum?

message.en_US: Well, apparently they didn't like the fact I'm always carrying this giant bell with me.
message.pt_BR: Bem, aparentemente eles não gostaram do fato de eu estar sempre carregando este sino gigante comigo.
message.zh_CN: 因为他们不喜欢我随身带着这个大钟的样子。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.ko_KR: 저들은 내가 이 거대한 종을 달고 다니는 게 싫었나 봐.<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.ja_JP:
まあ、明らかに、私がこの大きなベルを
いつも持ち歩いているのが
悪いんでしょうね。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.de_DE: Tja, anscheinend hatten sie ein Problem mit der großen Glocke, die ich immer mit mir herumtrage.
message.zh_TW: 因為他們不喜歡我隨身帶著這個大鐘的樣子。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]

message.en_US: Because yes, yes...\. Libraries are quiet places.
message.pt_BR: Porque sim, claro...\. As bibliotecas são lugares silenciosos.
message.zh_CN: 原因我也理解...\.图书馆是个安静的地方。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.ko_KR: 당연하긴 해...\. 도서관은 언제나 조용한 곳이니까.<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.ja_JP:
なぜって、それはもちろん...\.
書庫っていうのは
静かな場所ですからね。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.de_DE: Und ja, natürlich.... Bibliotheken sind Orte der Ruhe.
message.zh_TW: 原因我也理解...\.圖書館是個安靜的地方。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]

message.en_US: I know!
message.pt_BR: Eu sei!
message.ja_JP: わかってますとも！<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.de_DE: Das weiß ich doch!

message.en_US: What do they expect me to do?\. Constantly ring the bell like a crazy person?
message.pt_BR: O que eles achavam que eu ia fazer?\. Tocar o sino sem parar como um louco?
message.zh_CN: 他们以为我是疯子吗?\.到处乱敲钟?<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.ko_KR: 내가 어떻게 할 거라고 생각한 거야?\. 미친 사람처럼 온종일 종이라도 흔들고 다닐까 봐?<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.ja_JP:
私に何を期待してるっていうんです？\.
イカれたやつみたいにこのベルを
鳴らし続けろとでも？<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.de_DE: Wovor hatten die denn Angst? Dass ich wie ein Bekloppter mit der Glocke läute?
message.zh_TW: 他們以為我是瘋子嗎?\.到處亂敲鐘?<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]

message.en_US: Of course I wouldn't do that!
message.pt_BR: É claro que eu não faria isso!
message.ja_JP: そんなことするわけがないでしょう！<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.de_DE: Das würde ich doch nie tun!

message.en_US: But I just...\. have to bring it with me, okay?\. It's complicated.
message.pt_BR: Mas eu só...\. preciso carregar isso comigo, ok?\. É compliado.
message.zh_CN: 但是...\.这个钟我必须随身携带。\.理由很复杂。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.ko_KR: 난 그저...\. 이걸 가지고 다녀야 할 뿐이라고, 응?\. 복잡한 문제야.<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.ja_JP:
とはいえ...\.私はこのベルを
持ち歩く必要があるんです。
わかりますか？\.
複雑な事情があるんです。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.de_DE: Aber...\. ich muss sie einfach mit mir herumtragen.\. Es ist kompliziert, okay?
message.zh_TW: 但是...\.這個鐘我必須隨身攜帶。\.理由很複雜。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]

message.en_US: Well at least in this book store they don't mind.
message.pt_BR: Bem, pelo menos nessa livraria eles não se importam com isso.
message.zh_CN: 起码我在这个小书店里他们不会介意。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.ko_KR: 뭐, 최소한 이 서점에서는 신경 안 쓰니까.<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.ja_JP:
まあ、この本屋の中にいる限り、
誰も気にしないでしょう。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
message.de_DE: Na ja, zumindest hier im Buchladen wird die Glocke toleriert.
message.zh_TW: 起碼我在這個小書店裡他們不會介意。<<A<<[CHANGED 2019/04/16]
